                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13508845" author="ben.craig" created="Mon, 3 Dec 2012 16:43:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t know if it currently configurable in Thrift to change from static -&amp;gt; dynamic, but please don&apos;t force dynamic dependencies.  I&apos;m great with letting dynamic boost deps be an option, but I don&apos;t want to deal with the extra deployment complexity when shipping Thrift.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13664797" author="busbey" created="Thu, 23 May 2013 02:26:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;reproduced on CentOS 6.4 64bit, with boost-devel and boost installed via yum according to &lt;a href=&quot;http://thrift.apache.org/docs/install/centos/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;the docs for installing thrift on CentOS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13664904" author="jfarrell" created="Thu, 23 May 2013 05:59:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Have an update for this that is working for latest centos, testing on all systems/configurations now before posting patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13922423" author="hua zhang" created="Thu, 6 Mar 2014 12:31:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have the same problem, on centos 64bit. thrift-0.9.1&lt;br/&gt;
can someone resolve it?thank you very much&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13991375" author="patozzy" created="Wed, 7 May 2014 00:01:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have the same issue, after install boost-static (which is not a dependency according to the readme), I found the file in /usr/lib64.  linking the file to /usr/lib worked around the immediate issue but &apos;make check&apos; still failed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is centos supported by thrift?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13991457" author="jfarrell" created="Wed, 7 May 2014 01:26:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=patozzy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;patozzy&quot;&gt;patozzy&lt;/a&gt;, centos is definitely supported by Apache Thrift and works as expected (ran Thrift on centos in production at my previous company for over 4 years with no problems). i&apos;ll update the docs &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13992510" author="roger.meier" created="Thu, 8 May 2014 05:07:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;support lib64 and lib is supported by the upstream macro since this commit:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/autoconf-archive.git/commit/m4/ax_boost_base.m4?id=99c1ff5504f5c68dd94fc0f0fcfa0594e5340efb&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/autoconf-archive.git/commit/m4/ax_boost_base.m4?id=99c1ff5504f5c68dd94fc0f0fcfa0594e5340efb&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
This should fix the issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve updated aclocal/ax_boost_base.m4 and test is in progress.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13994588" author="roger.meier" created="Sun, 11 May 2014 15:42:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;could somone please test this patch &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12644344/12644344_0001-THRIFT-1771-make-check-fails-on-x64-for-libboost_uni.patch&quot; title=&quot;0001-THRIFT-1771-make-check-fails-on-x64-for-libboost_uni.patch attached to THRIFT-1771&quot;&gt;0001-THRIFT-1771-make-check-fails-on-x64-for-libboost_uni.patch&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13996939" author="roger.meier" created="Tue, 13 May 2014 21:49:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;update ax_boost_base.m4 from &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.gnu.org/software/autoconf-archive/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.gnu.org/software/autoconf-archive/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;br/&gt;
-roger&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13999037" author="hudson" created="Thu, 15 May 2014 18:24:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FAILURE: Integrated in Thrift #1152 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Thrift/1152/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Thrift/1152/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1771&quot; title=&quot;&amp;quot;make check&amp;quot; fails on x64 for libboost_unit_test_framework.a&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-1771&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-1771&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &quot;make check&quot; fails on x64 for libboost_unit_test_framework.a (roger: rev 73b58a24699eb6b9d43ad05f8a19cd084979c31a)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;aclocal/ax_boost_base.m4&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lib/cpp/test/Makefile.am&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14259031" author="jensg" created="Fri, 26 Dec 2014 10:45:28 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t know if it currently configurable in Thrift to change from static -&amp;gt; dynamic, but please don&apos;t force dynamic dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it&apos;s not so much about forcing. If any, then it is the static libs that are enforced because the Makefile linkes against e.g. libboost_unit_test_framework.a instead of libboost_unit_test_framework. It seems that some maintainers are going towards preferring the .so libraries. Just one example from some more I found: &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://forums.gentoo.org/viewtopic-t-730625-start-0.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Static linking is generally discouraged ...&lt;/a&gt;&quot;. Sure, I can always build the libs from source, but ...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
